stream
BT /F1 10 Tf 50 780 Td 13 TL
(SITE PROCEDURE SOP-ELEC-07 REV 4) Tj T*
(ELECTRICAL ISOLATION AND MCC ACCESS) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1. SCOPE) Tj T*
(This procedure applies to all work on motor control centers \(MCC\),) Tj T*
(including opening any MCC bucket, resetting breakers, and inspecting) Tj T*
(motor starters or drives.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(2. LOCKOUT/TAGOUT \(LOTO\) - MANDATORY) Tj T*
(Lockout/Tagout is required before opening any MCC bucket.) Tj T*
(Steps:) Tj T*
(2.1 Obtain a LOTO permit from the shift supervisor.) Tj T*
(2.2 Identify the isolation point on the drawing \(breaker or disconnect\).) Tj T*
(2.3 Open, lock and tag the breaker. Apply personal lock.) Tj T*
(2.4 Verify zero energy with a rated tester at the bucket terminals.) Tj T*
(2.5 Record permit number and isolation verification on the permit.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3. RESET AND RE-ENERGIZATION) Tj T*
(3.1 Breaker or drive resets require supervisor authorization.) Tj T*
(3.2 A completed LOTO permit must be attached to the work order.) Tj T*
(3.3 After reset, monitor the first start from a safe position.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4. ESCALATION) Tj T*
(If a fault trips again after one authorized reset, stop work and) Tj T*
(escalate to the reliability engineer. Do not attempt repeated resets.) Tj T*
ET
endstream
